Build Decoy Server to Confuse Defenders
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Deploy a realistic decoy server that mimics legitimate business services
Implement traffic obfuscation techniques to blend malicious activity with normal traffic
Create automated scripts for decoy server management and monitoring
Analyze log patterns to understand how decoys mislead defensive teams
Apply evasion techniques using decoy infrastructure in red team operations
Prerequisites
Before starting this lab, students should have:

Basic Linux command line proficiency
Understanding of networking concepts (TCP/IP, HTTP, ports)
Fundamental Python programming skills
Familiarity with web servers and system logs
